summary: If not turning a blind eye to all the potential signs of abuse makes me a "bad fan" - I'm all for it. If not ignoring all the...
question: If not turning a blind eye to all the potential signs of abuse makes me a "bad fan" - I'm all for it. If not ignoring all the obvious lies and inconsistencies in the narrative makes me a "bad fan" - I'm good with that. If not following the rules nans have put down about what I can and can't talk about makes me a "bad fan" - I'm happy to be labeled as such. If being a "good fan" means walking around his neighborhood, showing up wherever he is, stealing his used champagne and tissues - no thanks.

summary: Thinking about what kind of ring Stephen would buy to propose to Tony, I know he is the protector of Time stone, I assume he...
body:
Thinking about what kind of ring Stephen would buy to propose to Tony, I know he is the protector of Time stone, I assume he must grow accustom to the color of it, then It would only make sense for him to favor green gem stone,

also he would think about blue, because arc reactor is blue, Tony’s symbolic heart.

but he is also trying to detach himself for unnecessary material stuff, he didn’t really fancy expensive things anymore but also want to give the billionenaire something that would match his overall outfits always because he will wear that for the rest of his life.

Based on that consideration, I think he would buy something with green sapphire stone because green sapphire is colored by traces of iron but also blue gem (blue sapphire or diamond) stone for the arch reactor reminder. With palladium base ring perhaps (maybe even asking for a little bit of vibranium to T'challa for this special occasion).

So I am thinking a wedding ring with big jewel blue sapphire as the center and smaller green sapphire would adorn the rest of the ring like a support for the blue one.

Something like this :

I couldn’t decide if they would engrave Stephen♡Tony on the ring or timeless love with infinity symbol

You might think it’s too much jewels on a man ring, but hear me out

It looks just fine right?

Also thanks to @nubaerj for her edits and making my imagination came true seeing Tony and Stephen in their matching wedding rings.

Perfect right? 🥰

The ironstrange wedding ring in my Safe Haven fic on AO3
